<FIRST>d a PM-BRF--JunkFax     06-28 0118</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-BRF--Junk Fax,0120</SECOND>
<HEAD>New York Legislature Passes Daytime Junk Fax Ban</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ALBANY, N.Y. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The state Assembly has passed a bill forcing
purveyors of so-called junk fax to send the unwanted facsimile
transmissions only at night throughout New York.
   The partial ban, a compromise given final legislative approval
Tuesday, limits the transmission of unsolicited fax messages to 9
p.m. to 6 a.m., or during business hours between companies with a
longstanding business relationship. Violators would be subject to
$100 fines.
   The bill now goes to Gov. Mario Cuomo for his signature.
   Two other states have passed some kind of facsimile limitations,
and as least eight other states as well as Congress are looking at
fax caps.
</TEXT>
