<FIRST>u a AM-ForestFire     06-28 0175</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Forest Fire,0179</SECOND>
<HEAD>Forces Evacuation of Prison, Nudist Camp</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: Cele Cundari is cq</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CLEVELAND NATIONAL FOREST, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A 3,000-acre wildfire
roared through dense chaparral here Tuesday, threatening buildings
and prompting the evacuation of campgrounds, a prison and a nudist
camp, authorities said.
   No structural damage or injuries were reported from the blaze,
which was reported at around 3:15 p.m. on the border of Orange and
Riverside counties, said Cele Cundari of the U.S. Forest Service.
   Evacuations were called for the Convail Nudist Camp, the Ortega
Campground, Los Pinos Camp correctional facility, and residents of
Morrell Canyon and the small community of El Carriso Village, Ms.
Cundari said.
   Three fingers of flame were heading northeast, threatening about
100 buildings, she said.
   ``It's very steep and rocky, and the winds are very erratic,''
she said. ``They come down the canyons, plus the fire builds its own
winds, and it could change direction.''
   About 200 firefighters were on the scene, with 400 others
scheduled to be called in from around the state, she said.
