<SECOND>PM-People-Dukakis,0118</SECOND>
<HEAD>Oxford Reportedly Invites Dukakises</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BOSTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Oxford University has invited Gov. Michael S.
Dukakis and his wife, Kitty, to teach there for one term when he
leaves office next year, Mrs. Dukakis said.
   In an interview published today, Mrs. Dukakis told The Boston
Globe that she and her husband have not decided whether to accept
the offer.
   Mrs. Dukakis made her comments in Dublin, Ireland, where she is
visiting.
   In Boston, gubernatorial spokeswoman Susan Kaplan said Dukakis
did not know of an offer from Oxford.
   ``If the offer has been made, the governor is totally unaware of
it and is spending all his energy working on the budget,'' she said.
