<FIRST>r i PM-BRF--China-Blast     06-28 0113</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-BRF--China-Blast,0115</SECOND>
<UNK>Twenty-Two Die In Mine Explosion</UNK>
<DATELINE>BEIJING (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A gas explosion in a small coal mine in central
China killed 22 people and injured three, the official Xinhua News
Agency reported today.
   It quoted the Shanxi province's Coal Industry Bureau as saying
the explosion occurred Saturday in a village-run coal mine in the
suburbs of Jincheng, a city 370 miles southwest of Beijing.
   The cause of the explosion was under investigation, Xinhua said.
   Coal mine disasters are common in China, where most mines lack
modern equipment and safety provisions.
   More than 4,000 miners died in accidents in 1988, the worst year
for mine disasters in 40 years of communist rule.
