<FIRST>r i PM-Israel-Bomb     06-28 0240</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Israel-Bomb,0248</SECOND>
<HEAD>Four Wounded In Bomb Blast, Two Arabs Stabbed In Apparent Retaliation</HEAD>
<DATELINE>JERUSALEM (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A bomb exploded today in a garbage bin in the
central Israeli city of Ramle, slightly wounding four people, and
two Arabs were stabbed moments later in apparent revenge, police and
hospital officials said.
   The explosion occured at 11:15 a.m. on the main street of Ramle,
which was crowded with shoppers for the weekly open-air fruit and
vegetable market.
   Paramilitary border police were rushed to the city 12 miles east
of Tel Aviv to prevent further violence. The city has about 7,000
Arab residents among its 44,000 population.
   The four victims of the blast suffered minor injuries, according
to officials at Ramle Hospital.
   Two Arabs were stabbed in the legs at the market moments later by
Israelis angered by the blast, police sources said. They said two
Israelis were arrested for the stabbings.
   The Arabs victims were taken to Ramle Hospital but were not
believed to have been seriously hurt, the sources said, insisting on
anonymity.
   ``I heard a tremendous explosion. I saw a large cloud of smoke
and people running in all directions,'' Mordechai Levy, a shop owner
near the scene of the blast, said on Israel Army radio.
   He said many Palestinians from the occupied territories brought
produce to the market to sell on Wednesdays.
   Police cordoned off the area but had made no immediate arrests in
connection with the explosion.
</TEXT>
