<TEXT>
   Serenaded by Eddie Fisher, about 700 people
turned out to celebrate former Mayor Dianne Feinstein's 56th
birthday and to boost her campaign for governor.
   The event Tuesday night at the Fairmont Hotel raised $350,000 to
help Feinstein campaign against state Attorney General John Van de
Kamp for the Democratic nomination to run for governor next year
against the likely Republican candidate, Sen. Pete Wilson.
