<DATELINE>EUREKA SPRINGS, Ark. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   When a magazine interviewed Mayor
Richard Schoeninger for an article on what noted Arkansans do under
the sun, his answer was au naturel. He posed nude at his favorite
swimming hole.
   ``I'm a little bit mischievous and it was lots of fun,''
Schoeninger said Wednesday.
   A strategically placed boulder protected his modesty in the
photograph, which appears in the July issue of Arkansas Times
magazine. Nevertheless, the admittedly eccentric mayor was chastised
at a council meeting Tuesday by Alderman Susie Bell.
   ``It comes to a point in which one's uniqueness can interfere
with the job we are trying to do,'' she said.
