<FIRST>r i AM-Cuba-Tanker     06-28 0155</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Cuba-Tanker,0159</SECOND>
<HEAD>Burning Cuban Tanker Towed Out of Havana Harbor</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MEXICO CITY (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A tanker carrying about 3,000 tons of gasoline
caught fire in Havana harbor and was being towed out to sea
Wednesday to be destroyed because it was in danger of exploding, the
Cuban news agency reported.
   ``Firefighting units from the Interior Ministry are towing the
vessel at least five miles out to sea ... where helicopter gunships
will fire several rounds at it to cause an explosion,'' Prensa
Latina said.
   The tanker, August 23rd, caught fire Tuesday night while docked
at the Nico Lopez refinery, Prensa Latina said in a dispatch from
Havana that was monitored in Mexico City.
   ``The (Havana) port captain's office has banned all navigation in
a radius of five miles around the boat,'' the agency said. ``The
cause of the fire is being investigated.''
   The agency said Cuba purchased the tanker from Romania a year ago.
</TEXT>
