<HEAD>Thief Who Stole From U.S. Consulate Executed</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BEIJING (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A 36-year-old man who burglarized the U.S.
Consulate in Shanghai four times was executed Wednesday, the
official Xinhua News Agency said.
   Zhang Ping, a self-employed taxi driver, stole goods worth more
than $8,100 from the consulate between October 1986 and February
1988, Xinhua said.
   Zhang, who once served three years in prison for larceny, was
sentenced to death in April, and the Shanghai Higher People's Court
rejected Zhang's appeal June 24, the report said.
   Execution in China is carried out by a pistol shot to the back of
the head. Crimes involving foreigners are generally given harsher
sentences than if they involve Chinese.
