<HEAD>Fitzwater Says Bush ``Facing Another Successful Election''</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   White House spokesman Marlin Fitzwater seemed
to throw President Bush's hat into the 1992 presidential ring on
Wednesday when he declared Bush is ``facing another successful
election and another four-year term.''
   The subject came up as Fitzwater fielded questions on Bush's
support for a constitutional amendment to forbid flag burning.
   What other constitutional amendents did Bush favor? Fitzwater
rattled them off: balanced budget, line-item veto and a ban on
