<TEXT>
   An Wang, founder of Wang Laboratories Inc.,
is being treated for a malignant tumor of the esophagus, the company
and the Wang family announced Wednesday.
   The 69-year-old chairman of the board has responded positively to
chemotherapy and is scheduled to have the tumor removed at
Massachusetts General Hospital on July 14, the company said in a
statement.
   Chemotherapy followed by surgery has increased the cure rate of
esophageal cancer, a hospital spokesman said.
   The company will continue to be run by Frederick A. Wang,
president and chief operating officer.
