<TEXT>
   Stock prices rose Tuesday on the strength of declining interest
rates and rising oil company shares. The Dow Jones average of 30
industrials rose 14.99 to 2,526.37.
   U.S. Treasury bond yields fell to two-year lows on sentiment that
the economy is slowing and interest rates are declining.
   The dollar drifted lower against all major currencies except the
Japanese yen.
   Wheat futures prices bounded to a six-week high on the Chicago
Board of Trade. Livestock and meat futures were mostly lower while
oil and precious-metals futures were mixed.
