<FIRST>r f PM-PRMerger     06-28 0118</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-PR Merger,0126</SECOND>
<HEAD>Shandwick Acquires Dorf &amp; Stanton</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Shandwick PLC of London, the world's largest
independent public relations concern, has acquired New York-based
Dorf &amp; Stanton Communications Inc., the companies said.
   Terms of the transaction, announced Tuesday, were not disclosed.
   The sale includes two Dorf &amp; Stanton wholly-owned subsidiaries,
Gary Ferguson Associates of St. Louis and Pezzano + Co. of New York.
   No management or operational changes are anticipated, the company
said.
   Dorf &amp; Stanton is the eighth largest U.S. independent public
relations agency with 1988 billings of $7.5 million.
   The acquisition is the 16th in the United States for Shandwick,
whose billings exceed $140 million worldwide and $80 million in this
country.
</TEXT>
