<FIRST>r f PM-TreasuryAuction     06-28 0100</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Treasury Auction,0104</SECOND>
<HEAD>Yields on 2-Year Notes Fall to Lowest Level in Year</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Yields on 2-year Treasury notes fell in
Tuesday's auction to the lowest level in a year.
   The average yield was 8.26 percent, down from 8.84 at the last
comparable auction on May 24.
   It was the lowest rate since 2-year notes averaged 8.05 percent
on June 22, 1988. The notes will carry a coupon interest rate of 8\
percent with each $10,000 in face value selling for $9,998.20.
   A total of $8.76 billion in notes were sold out of bids totaling
$23.2 billion.
