<FILEID>AP-NR-06-28-89 0325EST</FILEID>
<FIRST>r f PM-CoorsAd     06-28 0332</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Coors Ad,0343</SECOND>
<HEAD>Beer-Maker Dropping TV Ad Offensive To Some Polish-Americans</HEAD>
<DATELINE>GOLDEN, Colo. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Adolph Coors Co. said it will drop a
television commercial that a New York Polish-American leader says
makes fun of Polish music and heritage.
   ``We're concerned there are some consumers out there who were
offended by it,'' said Coors spokesman Joe Fuentes. ```We never
intended that. We're going to drop the commercial. We're going to
apologize for any concern that it may have caused.''
   Edward Ostrowski, a past grand marshal of New York's Pulaski Day
Parade, said he would continue to push for a boycott of Coors
products despite Fuentes' comments.
   ``They told me they were going to drop it a week ago,'' Ostrowski
said in a telephone interview from New York. ``They're still showing
it. ... I think it was a slap in the face of the Polish people.
   ``It makes fun of our national music and our heritage. It's a
disgusting variation of Polish jokes and demonstrates an amazing
lack of sensitivity not only by Coors officials, but also by the ad
agency who devised this piece of trash.''
   Fuentes said the commercial for Coors Extra Gold beer was part of
a series by the Golden-based brewer called ``Party Time Tips.''
   Set in a singles rock n' roll bar, actor Tom Arcuragi, a polka
fan, said he had a tip for patrons who have trouble reaching the bar
to get another Coors Extra Gold. He then goes to the jukebox and
plays a polka and the bar empties out.
   Arcuragi played in a polka band for six years, Fuentes said.
   ``It was not our intention to offend anyone,'' he said. ``It was
designed to take a humorous look at a slice of American life. We're
just kind of exaggerating the music preference.''
   Ostrowski said the United Polka Artists first brought the
commercial to his attention. He said he would not drop his call for
a boycott until Coors officials ``call me personally and apologize.''
</TEXT>
</DOC>
