<HEAD>Corporate Parent Puts Color Tile on the Sale Block</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Knoll International Holdings Inc. said Wednesday
it intends to sell Color Tile Inc., a major retailer of floor
coverings with 700 stores nationwide.
   Knoll, a private holding company that owns an office-furniture
manufacturer and New York's ``21'' Club, said the divestiture of
Color Tile will allow it to focus on other business opportunities.
It did not say how much it would seek for the company.
   Color Tile was established in 1953 and grew into a national chain
selling floor coverings and related products, such as ceramic tiles,
wood flooring, carpet and wall coverings.
   Color Tile had sales last year of $433.9 million, after
adjustment for the sale of its Canadian subsidiary, according to a
spokeswoman for Knoll.
   Knoll acquired Color Tile in 1986 for an undisclosed price.
   New York-based Knoll also owns three companies that produce
polyurethane foam for various industrial uses and a leather
manufacturer and importer based in Canada.
