<HEAD>Tambrands To Buy Back Shares, Consider Selling Certain Units</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LAKE SUCCESS, N.Y. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Tambrands Inc. said Wednesday that its
board of directors had authorized the repurchase of up to 1.125
million shares of its stock, and that it was considering selling its
diagnostics and cosmetics operations.
   Tambrands, which makes Tampax tampons and other personal-care
products, said the share buyback could equal up to 5 percent of its
